ance-code/>.






Classification: Sensitive
From: raffaellanz@icloud.com <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Thursday, 6 November 2025 10:31 am
To: Lance O'Riley <Lance.ORiley@tower.co.nz>; Claims <Claims@tower.co.nz>
Cc: Abigail Collin <Abigail.Collin@wynnwilliams.co.nz>; Richard Hargreaves =
<Richard.Hargreaves@wynnwilliams.co.nz>; Zach Pion <Zach.Pion@tower.co.nz>
Subject: Overdue Temporary Accommodation Refund - Action Required ASAP
Importance: High

Hi Lance / Tower Claims, I=E2=80=99m writing about my temporary accommodati=
on refund submitted on 9 October 2025 under the content insurance claim, wh=
ich remains unpaid. On 2 September 2025, Tower confirmed the remaining amou=
nt under my temporary accommodation

Hi Lance / Tower Claims,

I=E2=80=99m writing about my temporary accommodation refund submitted on 9 =
October 2025 under the content insurance claim, which remains unpaid.

On 2 September 2025, Tower confirmed the remaining amount under my temporar=
y accommodation benefit was $13,820.62. As at 6 November 2025 (20 business =
days since my submission), I have received no acknowledgement, no payment, =
and no progress update, despite repeated follow-ups. While previous refunds=
 of the same were acknowledged within about 3 business days and paid prompt=
ly.

In line with my policy commitment to prompt payment and the Fair Insurance =
Code obligations for timely communication, please:

  *   Process immediate payment of the temporary accommodation expenses sub=
mitted on 9 October 2025; and
  *   Confirm the payment date
Please also confirm in writing that, going forward, Tower will acknowledge =
each accommodation refund request within 10 business days, and pay promptly.

Kind regards,
Raffaella del Prete



________________________________

The information contained in this email message is confidential and may be =
legally privileged. If you are not the intended recipient, please note that=
 any use, dissemination, distribution, or reproduction of this message in a=
ny form whatsoever, is strictly prohibited. If you received this email in e=
rror, please notify me by return email, delete your copy, and accept my apo=
logies for any inconvenience caused. Please note that your receipt of this =
email from a Tower email address does not constitute our consent for you to=
 send any other electronic information to Tower by return, unless specifica=
lly stated otherwise.

